This code was written for Pythonista and says the best lane based on your location


Setup:
pip install untangle

Example XML Input:
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1ytLWhB7ep1Vu4BUNoksX6SBNjQQ5221aS04q7uRFrnU

Data Source:
http://www.dot.state.mn.us/tmc/trafficinfo/developers.html

Map to find station data:
http://www.dot.state.mn.us/tmc/trafficinfo/downloads/adr.pdf

Station lookup for Lat/Lon:
http://data.dot.state.mn.us/iris_xml/metro_config.xml.gz




Credit Code Source:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/52051503/how-to-find-shortest-distance-of-a-location-from-a-route-python

Code for gzip and file download used example but pending URL to credit source. 